    void SetupManager.changeColor​(NetColorPreparation playerColors)
    This method changes set the color of a player with the color selected by the player.
    void ServerController.updateColors​(ObservableObject observed, NetColorPreparation playerColors)
    This method receives a request from a client through its RemoteView and analyze if it's the player's turn and if it is the correct phase (the color phase), if this conditions are all true then the method calls the SetupManager, otherwise it calls the error handling method of the RemoteView.

    Methods in it.polimi.ingsw.network with parameters of type NetColorPreparation 
    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void RemoteView.handleColorRequest​(NetColorPreparation req, boolean error)
    It receives a well formed request of color, meaning that the color is one of the three available colors, the remote view cannot know if the color is already owned by another player or not, for this reason notifies the ServerController.
    private void ClientMessageListener.parseColorInput​(NetColorPreparation msg)
    This method parses the color messages sending them to the controller and it changes the network phase id a specific message arrives.
    private void ServerClientListenerThread.parseColorInput​(NetColorPreparation colorMessage)
    This function parses the input that arrives from the client in the color choice phase, if the client has sent a color of the game it calls the RemoteView handling method.
